%matplotlib inline
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.datasets import make_blobs
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import axes3d
from rerf.urerf import UnsupervisedRandomForest
from sklearn.cluster import AgglomerativeClustering
from sklearn.cluster import SpectralClustering
from sklearn.metrics import adjusted_rand_score

# creating dataset with 2 and 3 features, respectively
centers_2D=[(30,1.5),(0,0),(-25,1)]
X_2D, true_label_2D = make_blobs(n_samples=200, 
                                 n_features=2,
                                 centers=centers_2D, 
                                 cluster_std=4,
                                 shuffle=True, 
                                 random_state=0)
X_2D_NoNoise=X_2D
X_2D_HighNoise=X_2D+np.random.normal(0, 15, size=X_2D.shape)
X_2D_MediumNoise=X_2D+np.random.normal(0, 3, size=X_2D.shape)
X_2D_LowNoise=X_2D+np.random.normal(0, .5, size=X_2D.shape)

# plotting 2D data
f, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 15), sharex=True)
plt.subplot(2,2,1)
sns.scatterplot(X_2D[:,0],X_2D[:,1],hue=true_label_2D,edgecolor='black');
plt.xlabel('X')
plt.ylabel('Y')
plt.title('True labels for 2D data without noise')

# plotting 2D data with high noise
plt.subplot(2,2,2)
sns.scatterplot(X_2D_HighNoise[:,0],X_2D[:,1],hue=true_label_2D,edgecolor='black');
plt.xlabel('X')
plt.ylabel('Y')
plt.title('High noise')

# plotting 2D data with medium noise
plt.subplot(2,2,3)
sns.scatterplot(X_2D_MediumNoise[:,0],X_2D[:,1],hue=true_label_2D,edgecolor='black');
plt.xlabel('X')
plt.ylabel('Y')
plt.title('Medium noise')

# plotting 2D data with low noise
plt.subplot(2,2,4)
sns.scatterplot(X_2D_LowNoise[:,0],X_2D[:,1],hue=true_label_2D,edgecolor='black');
plt.xlabel('X')
plt.ylabel('Y')
plt.title('Low noise')
plt.show()

# Rand_Index_2D_HighNoise,cluster_HighNoise=agglomerative_clustering(15)
# Rand_Index_2D_MediumNoise,cluster_MediumNoise=agglomerative_clustering(3)
# Rand_Index_2D_LowNoise,cluster_LowNoise=agglomerative_clustering(.5)  

# Agglomerative clustering on 2D data
I = []
cluster=[]
Rand_Index_2D=[]

cluster_HighNoise=[]
Rand_Index_2D_HighNoise=[]

cluster_MediumNoise=[]
Rand_Index_2D_MediumNoise=[]

cluster_LowNoise=[]
Rand_Index_2D_LowNoise=[]

for i in range (0,30):
        I.append(i+1)
A_Agglomerative_2D = []
cluster_A_2D = []

A_Agglomerative_2D_HighNoise = []
cluster_A_2D_HighNoise = []

A_Agglomerative_2D_MediumNoise = []
cluster_A_2D_MediumNoise = []

A_Agglomerative_2D_LowNoise = []
cluster_A_2D_LowNoise = []

# 100 trials
for j in range(0,100):
    X_2D, true_label_2D = make_blobs(n_samples=200, 
                                 n_features=2,
                                 centers=centers_2D, 
                                 cluster_std=4,
                                 shuffle=True, 
                                 random_state=0)
    X_2D_HighNoise=X_2D+np.random.normal(0, 15, size=X_2D.shape)
    X_2D_MediumNoise=X_2D+np.random.normal(0, 3, size=X_2D.shape)
    X_2D_LowNoise=X_2D+np.random.normal(0, .5, size=X_2D.shape)
    
    clf = UnsupervisedRandomForest(projection_matrix="RerF", random_state=0)
    clf.fit(X_2D)
    sim_mat_2D = clf.transform()
    
    clf.fit(X_2D_HighNoise)
    sim_mat_2D_HighNoise = clf.transform()
    
    clf.fit(X_2D_MediumNoise)
    sim_mat_2D_MediumNoise = clf.transform()
    
    clf.fit(X_2D_LowNoise)
    sim_mat_2D_LowNoise = clf.transform()
    
    cluster_A_2D.append([])
    cluster_A_2D_HighNoise.append([])
    cluster_A_2D_MediumNoise.append([])
    cluster_A_2D_LowNoise.append([])
    
    A_Agglomerative_2D.append([])
    A_Agglomerative_2D_HighNoise.append([])
    A_Agglomerative_2D_MediumNoise.append([])
    A_Agglomerative_2D_LowNoise.append([])
      
    for i in range (0,30):
        cluster_A_2D[j].append(AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=i+1, affinity="precomputed", linkage="average"))
        predict_labels_A_2D = cluster_A_2D[j][i].fit_predict(1-sim_mat_2D)
        A_Agglomerative_2D[j].append(adjusted_rand_score(true_label_2D, predict_labels_A_2D))
        Rand_Index_2D.append(A_Agglomerative_2D[j][i])
        cluster.append(I[i])
        
        # applying clustering on data with high noise
        cluster_A_2D_HighNoise[j].append(AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=i+1, affinity="precomputed", linkage="average"))
        predict_labels_A_2D_HighNoise = cluster_A_2D_HighNoise[j][i].fit_predict(1-sim_mat_2D_HighNoise)
        A_Agglomerative_2D_HighNoise[j].append(adjusted_rand_score(true_label_2D, predict_labels_A_2D_HighNoise))
        Rand_Index_2D_HighNoise.append(A_Agglomerative_2D_HighNoise[j][i])
        
        # applying clustering on data with medium noise
        cluster_A_2D_MediumNoise[j].append(AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=i+1, affinity="precomputed", linkage="average"))
        predict_labels_A_2D_MediumNoise = cluster_A_2D_MediumNoise[j][i].fit_predict(1-sim_mat_2D_MediumNoise)
        A_Agglomerative_2D_MediumNoise[j].append(adjusted_rand_score(true_label_2D, predict_labels_A_2D_MediumNoise))
        Rand_Index_2D_MediumNoise.append(A_Agglomerative_2D_MediumNoise[j][i])
        
        # applying clustering on data with low noise
        cluster_A_2D_LowNoise[j].append(AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=i+1, affinity="precomputed", linkage="average"))
        predict_labels_A_2D_LowNoise = cluster_A_2D_LowNoise[j][i].fit_predict(1-sim_mat_2D_LowNoise)
        A_Agglomerative_2D_LowNoise[j].append(adjusted_rand_score(true_label_2D, predict_labels_A_2D_LowNoise))
        Rand_Index_2D_LowNoise.append(A_Agglomerative_2D_LowNoise[j][i])

# plotting ARI vs number of clusters for each level of noise separately

f, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 15), sharex=True)
plt.title('Comparing the Efficiency of Agglomerative Clstering with Varying Number of Clusters')
plt.subplot(2,2,1)
data_2D_NoNoise={'Number of Clusters':cluster,'ARI':Rand_Index_2D}
sns.lineplot(x='Number of Clusters',y='ARI',data=data_2D_NoNoise)
plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters')
plt.ylabel('ARI')
plt.title('No noise')
maxid = np.argmax(Rand_Index_2D) # The id of the peak (maximum of Rand_Index-2D)
print('The maximum value for ARI is '+str(Rand_Index_2D[maxid])+ ' and the number of clusters corresponding to this is '+str(cluster[maxid]))

plt.subplot(2,2,2)                 
data_2D_HighNoise={'Number of Clusters':cluster,'ARI':Rand_Index_2D_HighNoise}
sns.lineplot(x='Number of Clusters',y='ARI',data=data_2D_HighNoise)
plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters')
plt.ylabel('ARI')
plt.title('High noise')
maxid = np.argmax(Rand_Index_2D) 
print('The maximum value for ARI is '+str(Rand_Index_2D_HighNoise[maxid])+ ' and the number of clusters corresponding to this is '+str(cluster[maxid]))
                 
plt.subplot(2,2,3)                 
data_2D_MediumNoise={'Number of Clusters':cluster,'ARI':Rand_Index_2D_MediumNoise}
sns.lineplot(x='Number of Clusters',y='ARI',data=data_2D_MediumNoise)
plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters')
plt.ylabel('ARI')
plt.title('Medium noise')
maxid = np.argmax(Rand_Index_2D)
print('The maximum value for ARI is '+str(Rand_Index_2D_MediumNoise[maxid])+ ' and the number of clusters corresponding to this is '+str(cluster[maxid]))
           
plt.subplot(2,2,4)                 
data_2D_LowNoise={'Number of Clusters':cluster,'ARI':Rand_Index_2D_LowNoise}
sns.lineplot(x='Number of Clusters',y='ARI',data=data_2D_LowNoise)
plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters')
plt.ylabel('ARI')
plt.title('Low noise')
maxid = np.argmax(Rand_Index_2D)
print('The maximum value for ARI is '+str(Rand_Index_2D_LowNoise[maxid])+ ' and the number of clusters corresponding to this is '+str(cluster[maxid]))

for i in range(0,3000):

Total_Cluster_2D.extend(cluster)
Total_Cluster_2D.extend(cluster)
Total_Cluster_2D.extend(cluster)
